HEADWORD: Unshape
<hw>Un*shape</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>shape</ets>.]</ety> <def>To deprive of shape, or
of proper shape; to disorder; to confound; to derange.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
